OL,3,CWater company fine reduced by over 90%
OL,5,FWelsh Water (Dwr Cymru) has
OL,6,Fsuccessfully appealed a #1.3 million
OL,7,Ffine after pleading guilty to breaches
OL,8,Fof environmental permit conditions.
OL,10,FIn May, the company admitted to 15
OL,11,Fcharges and was handed the six-figure
OL,12,Ffine. However, following an appeal
OL,13,Fhearing at Caernarfon Crown Court, the
OL,14,Ffine was reduced to #120,000 - a
OL,15,Fdecrease of more than 90%.
OL,17,FThe company argued that the original
OL,18,Ffine was "excessive".
