OL,3,CWater company fine reduced by over 90%
OL,5,F"Nonetheless, we recognised our
OL,6,Fcompliance fell short during 2020/21,
OL,7,Fa time when so much was impacted by
OL,8,FCovid. We entered a guilty plea at the
OL,9,Fearliest opportunity and apologised at
OL,10,Fthe hearing."
OL,12,FOn 16 October 2024, at Llandudno
OL,13,FMagistrates' Court, Dwr Cymru pleaded
OL,14,Fguilty to 15 of 18 charges. By 17
OL,15,FDecember 2024, the company accepted
OL,16,Fthe remaining offences as Taken into
OL,17,FConsideration (TIC) charges.
